# Design system rules ŌĆö UI / styles

This is a short enforcement layer. The full visual contract ŌĆö every token, every type level, every chart palette, every component pattern ŌĆö is in [`docs/design.md`](../../docs/design.md). **Read it before adding any UI.**

## Hard rules (these get enforced in review)

1. **No raw hex.** No `#047857`, no `text-emerald-600`, no `bg-[#FFF]`. Use the named tokens in [`tailwind.config.ts`](../../tailwind.config.ts) (`primary`, `surface`, `success`, `error`, `on-surface-variant`, etc.).
2. **No raw px / ms / shadow strings in `.tsx` files.** Use spacing tokens (`p-lg`, `gap-md`), radius tokens (`rounded-lg`), shadow tokens (`shadow-card`, `shadow-elevated`), motion tokens (`duration-base`, `ease-standard`).
3. **No raw greys.** `text-on-surface-variant` is the only correct way to get a secondary text colour. `text-gray-500` is wrong; it isn't theme-aware.
4. **Numbers always use `tabular`.** Either `text-data tabular` (KPIs, hero numbers) or `text-body tabular` (inline figures). Never plain numbers in a column.
5. **Icons via `<Icon name="..." />` only.** Never inline `<span class="material-symbols-outlined">`.
6. **One `secondary` (sunlight amber) accent per screen, max.** It marks the most important thing. If everything is highlighted, nothing is.
7. **Currency / percent via `lib/format.ts`.** `formatCurrency`, `formatLakhCrore`, `formatPercent`, `formatYears`, `formatMW`, `formatTonnes`, `formatKWh`. Never `toLocaleString`, `toFixed`, or hand-rolled `Ōé╣`/`%` strings.

## Theme awareness

The app currently runs in light mode (`<html class="light">`) but every component must work in dark mode by **only using token names**. If you find yourself writing a conditional for theme, you're using the wrong token.

## Charts (Recharts)

When adding or editing a chart in `src/components/charts/`:

- Series 1 always uses `primary`.
- Categorical palette in [`docs/design.md`](../../docs/design.md) ┬¦9.1 ŌĆö use the colours in order.
- With Ōēź3 series, vary stroke style as well as colour (solid ŌåÆ dashed ŌåÆ dotted) for colour-blind safety.
- Use the standard axis/grid/tooltip styling in [`docs/design.md`](../../docs/design.md) ┬¦9.5 ŌĆö don't reinvent it per chart.
- Positive cash flow ŌåÆ `success`; negative ŌåÆ `error`; break-even marker ŌåÆ `secondary`; baseline reference ŌåÆ `outline` dashed `4 4`.

**Forbidden chart types**: 3D, true pie (use donut), dual-axis line, bubble, radial bar.

## Mobile

- Components must work at 360px wide.
- Tap targets Ōēź 48px (`h-touch-target`).
- Tables: `overflow-x-auto` + `sticky left-0 bg-surface` first column.
- Tooltips: tap-to-open on mobile (handled by `Tooltip` primitive ŌĆö don't reinvent).
- Numeric inputs: `inputmode="decimal"` for Ōé╣/%, `"numeric"` for years.

## Motion

- Hover/press: `duration-fast` (120ms).
- Enter/exit, panel toggles: `duration-base` (200ms).
- Modals/sheets: `duration-slow` (320ms) with `ease-emphasised`.
- `prefers-reduced-motion` is handled globally in `src/index.css` ŌĆö **don't override per component**, and never rely on transform-based animation to convey information.

## When you need something that isn't here

Add a token to `tailwind.config.ts` with a one-line comment explaining the use case. **Don't** hard-code a value. If the new token is reusable, also document it in `docs/design.md`. The doc is the contract ŌĆö code without an entry there is technical debt.

